#META# shelfmark: Firuzkuh 85
#META# collection: Afghanistan National Archives
#META# group: Firuzkuh Papers
#META# classification: Silver (given following internal peer review)
#META# primaryLanguage: New Persian (Arabic script)
#META# documentType: Administrative
#META# documentSubtype: Administrative: Receipt
#META# writingSupport: paper
#META# writingSupportDetails: fold lines :: holes :: pasted into Mirza Khwaja Muhammad’s notebook :: staining
#META# writingSupportNotes: Incomplete (left side missing); 2 fold lines, incomplete (left half missing), black ink, some discoloration of the paper.
#META# foldLinesCount: 2
#META# contentSummary: A fragmentary receipt indicating a payment made in wheat, although the specific quantity is lost due to damage, but likely around 30 *mann*. The names of the payer and the recipient are missing from the document. However, the mention of an order of payment (*barāt*) pertaining to a person named Rashīd al-Dīn can be found in the third line. The phrase can be completed as [*ba-ḥukm-i*] *barāt-i Rashīd al[-Dīn-i Akhrang*], who is also documented in another receipt (Firuzkuh 58).
